@deeptigp : I'm unable to reproduce, but perhaps you can provide some more information. Please try the following when you get a chance:

bazel build -s //tensorflow/core:version_info_gen

This should print out something like:

tensorflow/tools/git/gen_git_source.py --generate tensorflow/tools/git/gen/spec.json tensorflow/tools/git/gen/head tensorflow/tools/git/gen/branch_ref "bazel-out/local-fastbuild/genfiles/tensorflow/core/util/version_info.cc"'

If you can execute that snippet, it should print out the details of why the python script that generates version_info.cc failed. Let us know what that is, and we might be able to pinpoint the problem.

Thanks.

@deeptigp : I'm unable to reproduce, but perhaps you can provide some more information. Please try the following when you get a chance:

``` sh
bazel build -s //tensorflow/core:version_info_gen
```

This should print out something like:

``` sh
tensorflow/tools/git/gen_git_source.py --generate tensorflow/tools/git/gen/spec.json tensorflow/tools/git/gen/head tensorflow/tools/git/gen/branch_ref "bazel-out/local-fastbuild/genfiles/tensorflow/core/util/version_info.cc"'
```

If you can execute that snippet, it should print out the details of why the python script that generates `version_info.cc` failed. Let us know what that is, and we might be able to pinpoint the problem.

Thanks.
